# Per-workspace static secrets. Mounted read-only into the container at
# /home/solvo/.solvo/secrets.env and sourced by the entrypoint before
# `solvo heartbeat` starts. NEVER commit the real `secrets.env`.
#
# Copy this file to `secrets.env` and fill in the values you want this
# workspace's agent to have. Leave blank or remove the line for any
# credential the agent shouldn't have.

# GitHub — `gh` CLI uses GH_TOKEN; raw `git push` over HTTPS uses GITHUB_TOKEN.
# Setting both is fine.
# GH_TOKEN=
# GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Vercel — `vercel deploy --token=$VERCEL_TOKEN`
# VERCEL_TOKEN=

# Netlify — `netlify deploy --auth=$NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN`
# NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN=

# Cloudflare Pages — wrangler reads CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN from env;
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID is required for `wrangler pages deploy`.
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=

# 2Captcha (or compatible — anti-captcha.com works with the same scheme).
# Powers the `solve_captcha` skill so the agent can punch through
# reCAPTCHA / hCaptcha / Turnstile gates non-interactively. Costs ~$0.001
# per solve. The agent reads this from env; without it the skill
# returns "no key — manual solve only" and falls back to Computer Use.
# CAPTCHA_API_KEY=

# Resend — outbound email (transactional + marketing). Free 3000/mo.
# Sender domain must be verified in Resend dashboard before agent's
# emails leave spam. Pair with AGENT_EMAIL on the receive side.
# RESEND_API_KEY=

# Supabase — per-project Postgres + Auth + Storage. Each workspace
# normally gets its own project; put the URL/keys here (not in the
# global ~/.solvo/secrets.env) so workspaces stay isolated.
# Service key bypasses RLS — only use in server-side code paths.
# SUPABASE_URL=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# observe_external skill — pull external reality (pageviews, replies,
# PR state) into the tick on agent demand. Every var here is OPTIONAL;
# the skill renders a "no <X> credentials" segment per source instead
# of crashing when one is missing. Wire only the sources this
# workspace cares about.
#
# Vercel Analytics — pageviews + top paths for a deployed project.
#   VERCEL_TOKEN already declared above (reused). Add the project id
#   and (for team-scoped projects) the team id.
# VERCEL_PROJECT_ID=
# VERCEL_TEAM_ID=
#
# GoatCounter — privacy-respecting unique visit counter. SITE is the
# subdomain (e.g. `solvohq` for solvohq.goatcounter.com); TOKEN is an
# API key minted in dashboard -> Settings -> API.
# GOATCOUNTER_SITE=
# GOATCOUNTER_TOKEN=
#
# Railway affiliate dashboard — clicks / signups / earnings on the
# operator's affiliate code. Currently best-effort via GraphQL; the
# skill degrades gracefully if Railway changes the schema.
# RAILWAY_AFFILIATE_TOKEN=
#
# (Gmail + GitHub reuse AGENT_EMAIL_IMAP_* and GH_TOKEN/GITHUB_TOKEN
# already declared above.)

# Reddit — distribution channel. Two parallel paths:
#   PRAW (primary, ~200 tokens/call): needs all 5 vars below.
#   Browser fallback (Playwright, ~5000 tokens/call): only needs
#   USERNAME + PASSWORD; agent falls back here when PRAW hits CAPTCHA /
#   2FA / suspicious-IP challenges, or when reading page state PRAW
#   can't expose (e.g. "was my post removed by mod?").
# CLIENT_ID + CLIENT_SECRET are minted at https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps:
#   create app -> select "script" -> redirect uri http://localhost:8080
#   (unused but required). client_id is the 14-char string under the
#   app name; client_secret is the "secret" field.
# USER_AGENT is mandatory per Reddit's API rules — must be a
# recognizable string in the form "<app>/<version> by /u/<username>".
# REDDIT_USERNAME=
# REDDIT_PASSWORD=
# REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=
# REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=
# REDDIT_USER_AGENT=solvo-agent/0.1 by /u/<your-username>

# Bluesky (AT Protocol) — cross-wedge audience-warming channel, same
# SolvoHQ persona as the Reddit identity (display name "stale lockfile").
# Provisioning was HARD-BLOCKED 2026-05-16: bsky.social now sets
# phoneVerificationRequired:true and createAccount returns
# InvalidPhoneVerification; the bsky.app signup form also fails to render
# its input fields from a datacenter IP. See product/outreach.md
# "Bluesky channel substrate" for the full finding and re-attempt options.
# When a non-phone-gated path exists: HANDLE is the full
# <name>.bsky.social; DID is the did:plc:* identifier; APP_PASSWORD is the
# 19-char xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx form minted via
# com.atproto.server.createAppPassword (use this, NOT the login password,
# for API automation).
# BLUESKY_HANDLE=
# BLUESKY_DID=
# BLUESKY_EMAIL=
# BLUESKY_PASSWORD=
# BLUESKY_APP_PASSWORD=

# Collection rail — self-custodied EVM wallet (zero signup, zero KYC, no
# third party that can fail or freeze funds). Generated ONCE with ethers
# v6 and persisted into the real secrets.env; idempotent — never
# regenerate. SERVER-SIDE ONLY: never `NEXT_PUBLIC_`, never in the client
# bundle.
#   ADDRESS  — public receive address. Safe to read server-side, print,
#              or show a payer. The only value payment code needs.
#   PRIVKEY  — spend key. NEVER client-exposed, NEVER read by any
#              verification code path (collection verify is read-only).
# See code/README.md "Payments (collection rail)" for the integration
# contract and the documented limitation (balance-based, no per-invoice
# payer attribution).
# SOLVO_PAYOUT_WALLET_ADDRESS=
# SOLVO_PAYOUT_WALLET_PRIVKEY=
